criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age from 18 years;

          -  non-smokers;

          -  have good general health;

          -  present at least 20 natural teeth in the mouth, including the incisors, canines and
             premolars without restorations, crowns, gingival recession, anatomic defects,
             gingivitis e/or periodontitis.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  positive history of using antibiotic e/or anti-inflammatory drugs in the month
             previous to the initial consultation;

          -  positive history of allergies at using Triclosan;

          -  pregnant or lactating patients;

          -  patients in use of fixed orthodontic appliance.
